This is the README file for the GlassPlayerHost package.

This software comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.  See the file 'COPYING' for
details.

See the file 'INSTALL' for instructions on building GlassNet from source.

GlassNet is a system for controlling a fleet of deployed GlassPlayer
audio stream players. It consists of the following software components:

gncd(8) - GlassNet Client Daemon
This component is deployed on the individual stream receivers. It provides
communication with the centralized management framework and launches and
stops glassplayer(1) instances.

gnmc(1) - GlassNet Management Client
A GUI client used to manage and control the GlassNet system.
